{"info": {"author": "Ron Chang", "author_email": "ron.hsien.chang@gmail.com", "bugtrack_url": null, "classifiers": [], "description": "# Flask Database Pacemaker\n<a href=\"https://www.buymeacoffee.com/ronchang\" target=\"_blank\"><img src=\"https://www.buymeacoffee.com/assets/img/custom_images/orange_img.png\" alt=\"Buy Me A Coffee\" style=\"height: 41px !important;width: 174px !important;box-shadow: 0px 3px 2px 0px rgba(190, 190, 190, 0.5) !important;-webkit-box-shadow: 0px 3px 2px 0px rgba(190, 190, 190, 0.5) !important;\" align=\"right\"></a>\n\n  \n`python_requires>=3.6`  \n`Flask>=1.0.2`  \n`Flask-APScheduler>=1.11.0`  \n`Flask-SQLAlchemy>=2.3.2`  \n\n## - How to use\n\n- Set confing.py\n>`MODELS_PATH_LIST` __is required__  \n`POKE_DB_INTERVAL` default value which is __one hour__\n\n```python\nDB_PACEMAKER_SWITCH = True if os.environ['ENVIRONMENT'] == 'develop' else False\nMODELS_PATH_LIST = ['model_path.models']\nPOKE_DB_INTERVAL = 60 * 60  # seconds\n```\n\n- Import package at `app.py`\n\n```python\nfrom flask_dbpacemaker import DBPacemaker\n```\n\n- Append this after you declare `config` and `app`\n\n```python\nDBPacemaker.run(app=app, config=config, display=True)\n```\n\n- If you have a exist scheduler, you have to add it like this.\n```python\nDBPacemaker.run(app, config, True, secheduler=secheduler)\n```\n\nNote: The job permanent trigger is `'interval'`.\n\nCheers! \ud83c\udf89", "description_content_type": "text/markdown", "docs_url": null, "download_url": "", "downloads": {"last_day": -1, "last_month": -1, "last_week": -1}, "home_page": "https://github.com/Ron-Chang/flask_dbpacemaker", "keywords": "", "license": "MIT", "maintainer": "", "maintainer_email": "", "name": "Flask-DBPacemaker", "package_url": "https://pypi.org/project/Flask-DBPacemaker/", "platform": "", "project_url": "https://pypi.org/project/Flask-DBPacemaker/", "project_urls": {"Homepage": "https://github.com/Ron-Chang/flask_dbpacemaker"}, "release_url": "https://pypi.org/project/Flask-DBPacemaker/1.1.1/", "requires_dist": null, "requires_python": ">=3.6", "summary": "Hook db connection when you're running a long term sleep crawler assignment.", "version": "1.1.1", "yanked": false, "html_description": "<div class=\"project-description\">\n            <h1>Flask Database Pacemaker</h1>\n<p><a href=\"https://www.buymeacoffee.com/ronchang\" rel=\"nofollow\"><img align=\"right\" alt=\"Buy Me A Coffee\" src=\"https://warehouse-camo.ingress.cmh1.psfhosted.org/320bf793359f29544369a3f1ecd7ec6a07a5dcd6/68747470733a2f2f7777772e6275796d6561636f666665652e636f6d2f6173736574732f696d672f637573746f6d5f696d616765732f6f72616e67655f696d672e706e67\"></a></p>\n<p><code>python_requires&gt;=3.6</code><br>\n<code>Flask&gt;=1.0.2</code><br>\n<code>Flask-APScheduler&gt;=1.11.0</code><br>\n<code>Flask-SQLAlchemy&gt;=2.3.2</code></p>\n<h2>- How to use</h2>\n<ul>\n<li>Set confing.py</li>\n</ul>\n<blockquote>\n<p><code>MODELS_PATH_LIST</code> <strong>is required</strong><br>\n<code>POKE_DB_INTERVAL</code> default value which is <strong>one hour</strong></p>\n</blockquote>\n<pre><span class=\"n\">DB_PACEMAKER_SWITCH</span> <span class=\"o\">=</span> <span class=\"kc\">True</span> <span class=\"k\">if</span> <span class=\"n\">os</span><span class=\"o\">.</span><span class=\"n\">environ</span><span class=\"p\">[</span><span class=\"s1\">'ENVIRONMENT'</span><span class=\"p\">]</span> <span class=\"o\">==</span> <span class=\"s1\">'develop'</span> <span class=\"k\">else</span> <span class=\"kc\">False</span>\n<span class=\"n\">MODELS_PATH_LIST</span> <span class=\"o\">=</span> <span class=\"p\">[</span><span class=\"s1\">'model_path.models'</span><span class=\"p\">]</span>\n<span class=\"n\">POKE_DB_INTERVAL</span> <span class=\"o\">=</span> <span class=\"mi\">60</span> <span class=\"o\">*</span> <span class=\"mi\">60</span>  <span class=\"c1\"># seconds</span>\n</pre>\n<ul>\n<li>Import package at <code>app.py</code></li>\n</ul>\n<pre><span class=\"kn\">from</span> <span class=\"nn\">flask_dbpacemaker</span> <span class=\"kn\">import</span> <span class=\"n\">DBPacemaker</span>\n</pre>\n<ul>\n<li>Append this after you declare <code>config</code> and <code>app</code></li>\n</ul>\n<pre><span class=\"n\">DBPacemaker</span><span class=\"o\">.</span><span class=\"n\">run</span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"n\">app</span><span class=\"o\">=</span><span class=\"n\">app</span><span class=\"p\">,</span> <span class=\"n\">config</span><span class=\"o\">=</span><span class=\"n\">config</span><span class=\"p\">,</span> <span class=\"n\">display</span><span class=\"o\">=</span><span class=\"kc\">True</span><span class=\"p\">)</span>\n</pre>\n<ul>\n<li>If you have a exist scheduler, you have to add it like this.</li>\n</ul>\n<pre><span class=\"n\">DBPacemaker</span><span class=\"o\">.</span><span class=\"n\">run</span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"n\">app</span><span class=\"p\">,</span> <span class=\"n\">config</span><span class=\"p\">,</span> <span class=\"kc\">True</span><span class=\"p\">,</span> <span class=\"n\">secheduler</span><span class=\"o\">=</span><span class=\"n\">secheduler</span><span class=\"p\">)</span>\n</pre>\n<p>Note: The job permanent trigger is <code>'interval'</code>.</p>\n<p>Cheers! \ud83c\udf89</p>\n\n          </div>"}, "last_serial": 7030152, "releases": {"0.0.1": [{"comment_text": "", "digests": {"md5": "f515e103b6ec56abb5d4cfc81503e22a", "sha256": "775e45a4c7c2e0bd8318cfe6f151abff3f9e49fb41b3922e7d0388d433920a08"}, "downloads": -1, "filename": "Flask_DBPacemaker-0.0.1-py3-none-any.whl", "has_sig": false, "md5_digest": "f515e103b6ec56abb5d4cfc81503e22a", "packagetype": "bdist_wheel", "python_version": "py3", "requires_python": ">=3.6", "size": 2561, "upload_time": "2020-04-12T14:13:19", "upload_time_iso_8601": "2020-04-12T14:13:19.370784Z", "url": "https://files.pythonhosted.org/packages/df/c2/6a14992ee25aa245a15f78406573944baceb1f1bd8b42e50780fd0dbd105/Flask_DBPacemaker-0.0.1-py3-none-any.whl", "yanked": fals